  "sc:description": "Tools for clustering and enhancing the resolution of spatial gene expression experiments. BayesSpace clusters a low-dimensional representation of the gene expression matrix, incorporating a spatial prior to encourage neighboring spots to cluster together. The method can enhance the resolution of the low-dimensional representation into \"sub-spots\", for which features such as gene expression or cell type composition can be imputed.",
  "sc:license": "MIT",
  "sc:name": "BayesSpace",
  "sc:operatingSystem": [
    "Windows",
    "Linux",
    "Mac"
  ],
  "sc:softwareHelp": {
